title: "Sinopolonica: A Logographic-Latin Hybrid Writing System for Polish"
message: "If you reference this system, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Kowalczyk
    given-names: Marek Andrzej
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0008-3874-6736"
  - name: "Claude (Anthropic)"
date-released: "2026-03-28"
url: "https://github.com/marekkowalczyk/sinopolonica"
license: CC-BY-SA-4.0
keywords:
  - constructed script
  - Chinese characters
  - Polish language
  - logographic writing system
  - neography
  - fantasy linguistics
abstract: >
  Sinopolonica is a constructed writing system for Polish that pairs
  Classical Chinese logographic characters with Latin-script inflectional
  suffixes. Governed by five axioms and eighteen principles, the system
  exposes etymological structure, eliminates suppletive irregularity at
  the visual level, and encodes register through character source.
